children.content: Former US President Donald Trump filed a motion on Monday seeking to disqualify US District Judge Tanya Chutkan from presiding over the criminal case charging him with trying to overturn his 2020 presidential election loss.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: More bodies are being pulled from the rubble, in the worst affected earthquake zones in Morocco. Middle East Correspondent Allyson Horn filed this from the epicentre of the quake zone: "In the village of Talat N'Yaaqoub, nearly every single building is destroyed. This is ground zero – where homes and businesses have been demolished – thousands killed and many more bodies still buried under the rubble. "The survivors are sleeping on cardboard boxes on the bare earth, with nowhere else to go, hoping humanitarian aid will arrive soon. But so far, they're now living without food, running water, electricity and sanitation."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: More bodies being found in Morocco earthquake zones

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A Spanish High Court judge has opened an investigation into former Spanish Football Federation president Luis Rubiales, a day after he resigned from his role. Spain forward Jenni Hermoso filed a legal complaint last week over Rubiales kissing her on the lips following her country's Women's World Cup final win. Rubiales quit as a result of the controversy. A magistrate will be assigned to lead the investigation, which will determine if the case goes to trial or is dismissed.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: High court investigating Rubiales day after resignation
